<title type="html"><![CDATA[Marioland / Metroid 2 full colour romhacks]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9868&amp;p=108537#p108537"><![CDATA[
Myself and spikeman have been tag-teaming the gbcolorizer code and have managed to get colorized gb games running on real hardware:<br /><br /><img src="http://imgboot.com/images/Drakon/m2colourtitle.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br /><img src="http://imgboot.com/images/Drakon/m2colourruns.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Here's the patches in their current states.<br /><br />Metroid 2:<br /><br /><a href="http://www.mediafire.com/?2mw987yo0e7y5iw" class="postlink">http://www.mediafire.com/?2mw987yo0e7y5iw</a><br /><br />Marioland:<br /><br /><a href="http://www.romhacking.net/hacks/1187/" class="postlink">http://www.romhacking.net/hacks/1187/</a><br /><br />Spikeman is working on fixing that annoying random glitching tile bug.  Once that's fixed really these will be running flawlessly.  I'm currently getting people to playtest metroid 2 since I don't know the game very well and I figure someone with experience could plow through it much faster than myself.<br /><br />Hardware testing was done on a couple of gameboy devcarts I built.  My mbc 5 devcart supports uv eproms up to 1mbyte and dip flash chips up to 512k.  Also my mbc5 cart has the largest size sram and a battery circuit so it can save your game as well.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4533">Drakon</a> — Thu Feb 28, 2013 8:52 pm</p><hr />
